data.event_name: CPE Six Sigma and Project Management
data.summary: NJIT CPE Six Sigma and Project Management Training
data.description:
PMP/CAPM Exam Preparation "Boot Camp"
Description
This is an intensive course that will cover all 9 Knowledge Areas covered on thePMP exam and will highlight important terms and concepts that are "needto knows."  Students will also learn strategies for preparing for the exam and for answering exam questions.  A pre-test will be conducted in-class for each student to establish their own personal level of knowledge.  At the end of each module on a Knowledge Area\, students will take a practice test and answers will be reviewed.  At the end of the 5-days\, students will take a simulated comprehensive practice test covering all Knowledge Areas.

Six Sigma Green Belt
Description
Certified Six Sigma Green Belt professionals work on process improvement teams using the DMAIC approach: DEFINE\, MEASURE\, ANALYZE\, IMPROVE\, CONTROL. NJIT's Six Sigma Green Belt course gives you the knowledge\, skills and experience needed to use Six Sigma methods and tools\, and will help you advancetowards Six Sigma Green Belt Certification.  This course is based on the American Society for Quality (ASQ) Six Sigma Body of Knowledge\, and is taught by an ASQ Certified Six Sigma Black Belt instructor.

While this course will prepare students for the ASQ Six Sigma Green Belt exam\,it is recommended that you visit the ASQ website to make sure you meet the eligibility requirements to sit for the ASQ CSSGB Exam.

Six SigmaProject 
This course provides qualified students with the opportunity to form a team and work with other students\, under the mentorship of anAmerican Society for Quality Certified Six Sigma Black Belt\, to complete a real DMAIC (Define- Measure-Analyze-Improve-Control) Project.

The team will select\, and complete\, a real world project using a varietyof Lean Six Sigma tools\, which they are already familiar with. The instructor will review each LSS tool before the students apply it to the project.  The instructor will guide the students in the application of each tool to the project and the integration of tools within the project.  For more information or how to register for these courses please go to http://www.njit.edu/continuing/ 

Students should expect to perform work on the project both during and between class sessions.  This course may involve one or more field trips to the location where the process being improved is located.

Soccer Tennis consists of a net being set up between two teams and simply kicking/playing the ball back and forth over the net (tennis rules\, but using your feet and a soccer ball). It's a stationary activity and the players will not be wearing cleats\, only tennis shoes.
